dableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":"596","contextId":"8","url":"","type":"NMI_TYPE_CUSTOM","path":"przesylanie_tekstow","content":{"en_US":"<p>Already have a Username\\/Password for Studies of the Industrial Geography Commission of the Polish Geographical Society?<br><a class=\\"action\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/prace-kgp.up.krakow.pl\\/login\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">Go to Login<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Need a Username\\/Password?<br><a class=\\"action\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/prace-kgp.up.krakow.pl\\/user\\/register \\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">Go to Registration<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Registration and login are required to submit items online and to check the status of current submissions.<\\/p>","pl_PL":"<p>Posiadasz nazw\\u0119 u\\u017cytkownika oraz has\\u0142o do zalogowania si\\u0119 na stronie czasopisma Prace Komisji Geografii Przemys\\u0142u Polskiego Towarzystwa Geograficznego?<br><a class=\\"action\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/prace-kgp.up.krakow.pl\\/login \\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">Przejd\\u017a do logowania<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Nie posiadasz nazwy u\\u017cytkownika oraz has\\u0142a<br><a class=\\"action\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/prace-kgp.up.krakow.pl\\/user\\/register \\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">Przejd\\u017a do rejestracji<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Rejestracja oraz logowanie s\\u0105 niezb\\u0119dne do wysy\\u0142ania tekst\\u00f3w oraz sprawdzania ich aktualnego statusu.<\\/p>"},"title":{"en_US":"Submissions","pl_PL":"Przesy\\u0142anie tekst\\u00f3w"}},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[],"_data":{"id":"602","menuId":"54","menuItemId":"596","parentId":"606","seq":"25"},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":"597","contextId":"8","url":"","type":"NMI_TYPE_CUSTOM","path":"wytyczne_dla_autorow","content":{"en_US":"<div id=\\"authorGuidelines\\">\\r\\n<p>Studies of the Industrial Geography Commission of the Polish Geographical Society contain only original, previously unpublished research papers on issues directly associated with each given volume.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Each issue of the Studies of the Industrial Geography Commission of the Polish Geographical Society contains papers, which, among others, are based on the presentation of research results and discussion points at international research conferences held in Krak\\u00f3w since 1985 on the industrial and service sectors.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Summaries of papers discussed at conferences are published in a book of summaries.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The journal is registered in the Polish Register of newspapers and journals and indexed in Polish and international&nbsp;databases,&nbsp;including&nbsp;<strong>Web of Science&nbsp;<\\/strong>Core Collection&nbsp;<strong>- Emerging Source Citation Index<\\/strong>&nbsp;of&nbsp;Clarivate Analytics (formerly Thomson Reuters).<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We invite you to submit full-text papers in electronic form (using MS Word or *.rtf) in the Polish or English language. The papers should be formatted as described in this <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/prace-kgp.up.krakow.pl\\/$$$call$$$\\/api\\/file\\/file-api\\/download-library-file?libraryFileId=43 \\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">file<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Once your paper is printed, you will receive one paper version of your publication.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>For Polish-language texts, be sure to include a title, an abstract (1000-1500 characters with spaces), keywords (4-7) and a short biography of the author (300-1000 characters) in both the English language and Polish language. For English-language texts, be sure to include an abstract (1000-1500 characters), keywords (4-7) and a short biography of the author (300-1000 characters with spaces). The preferred paper length is 10-20 pages (18000-36000 characters with spaces).<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>It is especially important to clearly define the purpose of your paper. We also review the research methods used in your paper and the research literature discussed in your paper.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Basic formatting information:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">A4 page format (margins: upper 2 cm, lower 2 cm, left 1,5 cm, right 3,5 cm);<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">Standard font: Times New Roman 12 pts;<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">Paragraph format: spaces between lines - 1.5, justified text;<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">Figures, tables and diagrams should be black and white or degrees of grey and should be stored as separate files;<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">Text length: 10-20 pages, assuming that one page contains about 1800 characters with spaces. The page limit already includes the title, abstract, keywords and short biographical note in the English language. For Polish-language papers, the above should be in the Polish language. The entire paper should be formatted according to the above specifications. This includes graphs and tables.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Detailed formatting information can be found in this&nbsp;<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/prace-kgp.up.krakow.pl\\/$$$call$$$\\/api\\/file\\/file-api\\/download-library-file?libraryFileId=43 \\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">file<\\/a> or in <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/prace-kgp.up.krakow.pl\\/$$$call$$$\\/api\\/file\\/file-api\\/download-library-file?libraryFileId=42 \\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">article template<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>ATTENTION: not-applying above rules will extend publishing process and widely raise its costs; because of this reason the editorial office is reserving the option not to admit to the press works which will not comply with the principles of formatting. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Paper submission procedure:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">author submits a paper for publication \\u2013 formatted according to stated requirements \\u2013 via e-mail or the electronic submission system available on the journal\\u2019s website<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">Editorial Secretary checks if the paper meets all formal requirements \\u2013 matches the journal\\u2019s research profile, matches the subject matter of the given volume, possesses the right format \\u2013 and may require editing work by the author<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">Editorial Secretary confirms that a paper has been accepted for further processing<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">paper is reviewed from a science perspective by the Editor-in-Chief or Associate Editor and the Subject Editor \\u2013 a paper may be formally rejected or sent back to be edited or supplemented; in the event of a problem, the paper is sent by the Editor-in-Chief, Associate Editor or Subject Editor to a member of the Science Committee or another specialist knowledgeable in the field of interest<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">the paper is sent to two reviewers working with the double-blind review process; if the given paper is highly interdisciplinary or the two reviewers express very different opinions, then the paper may be sent to a third reviewer<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">the Editorial Secretary notifies the author when the review have arrived and sends the reviews to the author; suggestions made by the Editor-in-Chief, Associate Editor, Statistics Editor or Subject Editor may also be sent to the author, along with a deadline for an edited version of the paper<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">author submits an edited version of the paper, along with comments if he or she does not agree with the reviewers, as well as a declaration of copyright<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">the paper is accepted for publication following the review process and the author is notified of this fact by the Editorial Secretary; if the resubmitted paper has not been edited in a manner satisfactory to the reviewers or editors, it may be sent to more reviewers or returned to the author for more editing<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">language editing and typesetting; the author may be contacted if certain expressions are not entirely clear or certain figures need to be reworked<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">if a significant number of changes are made to the paper by the editors, it will be sent to the author for approval following the typesetting process along with a short deadline<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">the author is notified once a paper has been printed and will receive a personal copy<\\/li>\\r\\n<li class=\\"show\\">an electronic version of the paper will be placed in the journal\\u2019s online archive once all or most of the printed copies are gone<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n<p><strong>Cost of publication:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Papers are published free of charge.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Participants of the cycle of Krakow conferences devoted to the issues of industry and services <a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.industry.up.krakow.pl\\/?page_id=358\\">http:\\/\\/www.industry.up.krakow.pl<\\/a> have priority in publishing papers (fast-track peer review).<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Guidelines for the authors: <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/prace-kgp.up.krakow.pl\\/$$$call$$$\\/api\\/file\\/file-api\\/download-library-file?libraryFileId=42 \\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">doc<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/prace-kgp.up.krakow.pl\\/$$$call$$$\\/api\\/file\\/file-api\\/download-library-file?libraryFileId=43 \\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">pdf<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Conflict of interest and contribution of authors 